# Privacy Policy
Last Updated: March 2026

All Things CS ("the Bot") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected and how it is used when you use the bot.

## Information We Collect

The bot may store limited information necessary for its features to function. This may include:

• Discord Server IDs  
• Discord Channel IDs  
• Discord Role IDs  
• Configuration data required for bot features (such as news or update channels)

The bot **does not collect personal user data** such as messages, email addresses, passwords, or private information.

## How We Use Information

The information stored is used only to provide the bot's functionality, including:

• Posting Dust2 news updates  
• Posting CS2 update announcements  
• Configuring channels and roles for notifications  
• Operating bot commands

This data is used strictly for bot operation and service improvement.

## Data Storage

Configuration data may be stored locally or on the server hosting the bot. This data is only used to maintain bot functionality within Discord servers where the bot is installed.

## Data Sharing

All Things CS **does not sell, share, or distribute user data** to third parties.

The bot may use third-party services to provide information, including:

• BO3.gg  
• Steam Community  
• Dust2.us

These services operate under their own privacy policies.

## Data Removal

Server administrators may remove stored data by:

• Removing the bot from their server  
• Using configuration commands to disable features

Once removed, stored configuration data related to that server may be deleted.

## Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time to reflect changes to the bot or its services.

## Contact

If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, you may contact the developer through the GitHub repository for this project.
